Malosini-  The person pretty much has to be 6-8 levels lower than you and have total junk resists for this spell to land, useless in pvp.<br>
Shock of Steel- Doesn't seem to do very much dmg unless you mala them first, and even then the cast time is way long to use in pvp.<br>
Seeking Flame of Seukor- maneater, cast time is very long so use it to open up fights on opponents who dont know you are there yet.<br>
Manastorm-  In all the times I've casted only one person has not resisted every single wave. Useless<br>
Velocity- so sexy almost evil when you get a mastered water pet with a MR buff on it.<br>
Sirocco- Evil Evil Evil, I've killed 3 casters at once with this spell when they didn't move out from under it.  It's great for zoning into a dungeon and opening up with this spell in mass pvp.<br>
Scars of Sigil-  Pretty much the only spell you will consistently channel versus melees.  High resist rate and melees will laugh as they pound you.<br>
Char- Main pvp spell for me.  Reasonable cast time combined with an extremely low resist rate makes it the best compromise.<br>
Scintillation- Awesome spell for mass pvp.  I've gotten 16 hits at once with this spell before.  Low resist rate.<br>
<br>
Pets for pvp.<br>
Below level 34 I would use earth because most people won't have resist gear to resist roots.<br>
34 to 53 I would use fire or water.<br>
54 and 60 water pets are excellent pets for pvp.  The backstabs, nukes, and hard hits will rock someone.  The air pets are okay I guess, but the stun won't ever land.  The earth and fire pets are a waste of time, the fire pets especially are a joke in pvp with their gimp melee dmg and gimp nukes.<br>
<br>
Just my observations on mage pvp spell effectiveness in case anyone else was toying with spell combos for duels and stuff.<br>
